attachments.text: In place of Uber’s signature black, gray, and blue color palette, the company will embrace bright colors---lots of them.

text: Interesting read indeed. I find specially interesting that UX isn’t mentioned at all.

Yeah. Not sure how I feel about the art direction, but I think the idea of a brand that is both both distinct to the local area while always being rooted in the global brand is a a smart move. Captures the companies mission in it’s iconography.
The whole “bits and atoms” thing seems like a stretch
but can appreciate the systems thinking behind it
